  "description": "<i>Czarny Poniedzia?ek</i> (Black Monday) is a turn-based strategy game simulating a stock market. Each player (from 1 to 4) begins with 50000 dollars. Each turn, the player can buy or sell stocks, or simply skip a turn. The stock prices change after each turn. Skipping a turn causes a random event to happen, which makes the player slightly poorer or richer. It is also possible to check one's finances and owned stocks at any time, with no turn loss. The goal of the game is simply to gain as much money as possible. ",
